
## Lower Arm Ball Joint Removal Note  


Separate the ball joint from the knuckle by using the SST.  

![](images/0.jpg)
  


## Dust Boot Removal Note  


Carefully remove the dust boot by using a chisel.  

![](images/1.jpg)
  


## Lower Arm Bushing (Front and Rear) Removal Note  


Press the lower arm bushing out by using the SSTs and a socket as shown.  

![](images/2.jpg)
  


## Lower Arm Bushing (Front and Rear) Installation Note  


1. Apply soapy water to the lower arm bushing. 
2. Press the bushing in by using the SST and socket in the direction of the arrow.  

![](images/3.jpg)
  

![](images/4.jpg)
  


## Dust Boot Installation Note  


1. Wipe away the grease on the ball joint. 
2. Liberally coat the inside of the new dust boot with grease. 
3. Press the dust boot onto the ball joint by using the SST. 
4. Wipe away any grease that has been expelled from the dust boot.  

![](images/5.jpg)
